               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18431023-name-1469" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1469" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1469" type="surname" value="DANIELS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18431023-name-1469" type="given" value="MARY ANN"></interp>MARY ANN DANIELS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of William Daniels, and keep a public-house at Woolwich. On the 26th of Sept. I put my gold watch into the glass drawer on the table—I missed it about half-past two o'clock the same after<lb></lb>noon—this is it—the prisoner was there, helping to wait.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I was not a servant in the house, I was discharged the day be<lb></lb>fore. <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> I am sure he was in the house that day—he cleaned the pots.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18431023-name-1470" type="witnessName">
